5|$|Galileo {{put forward}} the basic {{principle}} <b>of</b> <b>relativity,</b> {{that the laws}} of physics are the same in any system that is moving at a constant speed in a straight line, regardless of its particular speed or direction. Hence, there is no absolute motion or absolute rest. This principle provided the basic framework for Newton's laws of motion and is central to Einstein's special theory <b>of</b> <b>relativity.</b>|$|E
