50|$|The {{mathematics}} <b>of</b> general <b>relativity</b> {{refers to}} various mathematical structures and techniques {{that are used}} in studying and formulating Albert Einstein's theory <b>of</b> general <b>relativity.</b> The main tools used in this geometrical theory of gravitation are tensor fields defined on a Lorentzian manifold representing spacetime. This article is a general description of the mathematics <b>of</b> general <b>relativity.</b>|$|R
